      "question": "The roots of the quadratic equation $x^2 - 11x + 28 = 0$ are obtained by splitting the middle term. Which of the following represents the correct factorization?",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the quadratic equation $x^2 - 11x + 28 = 0$.",
          "Find two numbers whose product is $28$ and whose sum is $-11$.",
          "The factors of $28$ are $(1, 28), (2, 14), (4, 7)$.",
          "Since the sum is $-11$, the numbers are $-4$ and $-7$.",
          "Rewrite the equation as $x^2 - 4x - 7x + 28 = 0$.",
          "Factor by grouping: $x(x - 4) - 7(x - 4) = 0$, which gives $(x - 4)(x - 7) = 0$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x^2 - 11x + 28 = 0 \\ x^2 - 4x - 7x + 28 = 0 \\ x(x - 4) - 7(x - 4) = 0 \\ (x - 4)(x - 7) = 0$"
      },
      "topic": "Quadratic Equations",
      "subtopic": "factorisation method",
      "marks": 1,
      "type": "mcq",
      "difficulty": "simple",
      "options": [
        "(A) $(x - 2)(x - 14) = 0$",
        "(B) $(x + 4)(x + 7) = 0$",
        "(C) $(x - 4)(x - 7) = 0$",
        "(D) $(x + 2)(x + 14) = 0$"
